text: A close-mid vowel (also known as mid-close vowel, high-mid vowel, mid-high vowel, or half-close vowel) is a class of vowel sounds used in some spoken languages. The tongue is placed about one-third from a close vowel to an open vowel for a close-mid vowel. ==List== The close-mid vowels that have symbols in the International Phonetic Alphabet are: * close-mid front unrounded vowel * close-mid front rounded vowel * close-mid central unrounded vowel (older publications may use ) * close-mid central rounded vowel (older publications may use ) * close-mid back unrounded vowel * close-mid back rounded vowel ==References== Category:Vowels
title: Close-mid vowel
